<section sectnbr = "6B">
<servcat sctnbr = "06" scnbr = "02">
<configtype typenbr = "0">
<servinfotype sitcode = "6">
<servinfo servinfosgmlid = "AENBP70A6206009" svcinfotypenbr = "08" svcinfoqualnbr = "01" page = "2" supplyoff = "1" modify = "0">
<title>
Steering Column Removal and Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A6206001">Steering Wheel and Column Components</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
The steering column assembly can be easily damaged during and after removal.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
To avoid damaging the steering column assembly, be sure to take the following precautions when removing it and when setting it down after removal:
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not release telescopic and tilt lever with steering column mounting nuts loosened or steering column removed from vehicle. Doing so may increase operating force for telescopic or tilt motion.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
The impact energy absorbing function of the steering column assembly may be impaired if the steering column assembly receives an excessively large force.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Be careful not to strongly impact the steering column assembly when removing and installing it.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Never drop the steering column assembly on its end. This could collapse the steering shaft or loosen capsules that maintain the design length of the column.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not lean the steering column assembly against something. This could cause it to bend or deform.
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Do not loosen the steering column mounting nuts with steering shaft joint upper side bolt tightened. This could cause damage to the steering shaft joint of steering column.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention4>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A6206009001">
<title>
Removal
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove contact coil assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6206003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove lighting switch and wiper switch.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Lighting switch: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9206019"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Wiper switch: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9406012"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering column hole cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove knee air bag (Inflator) module (if equipped). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A8206007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering joint cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6206001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering lower shaft. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6206015"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove instrument cluster panel (1). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect P/S control module connector (2).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "I9P60A620016.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "74.313mm" ver = "01" gw = "157" gh = "194"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Detach steering column harness clamps (1).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect P/S control module connector (2).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect steering lock connector (3).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering column mounting nuts (4) and reinforcement nut (5).
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B620002.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "78.458mm" ver = "01" gw = "165" gh = "206"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove steering column.
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
<servinfosub id = "AENBP70A6206009002">
<title>
Installation
</title>
<ptxt>
<intxrefpoff refid = "AENBP70A6206011">Steering Column Inspection</intxrefpoff>
</ptxt>
<attention4>
<ptxt>
Tightening the fasteners in the wrong order may cause damage to the steering shaft joint of steering column.
</ptxt>
<ptxt>
Be sure to tighten the steering column mounting nuts in the order given before installing the steering lower shaft.
</ptxt>
</attention4>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check that vehicle’s front wheels are at straight-ahead position.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install steering column. Then tighten steering column lower nuts (1) on lower side and then steering column upper nuts (2) on upper side to specified torque.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install reinforce nut (3) to specified torque.
</ptxt>
<attention3>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
When installing, make sure that clearance “a” between bolts (4) and bracket (5) should be 0 (zero).
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
After installing tilt steering column, make sure that steering column moves upwards and downwards smoothly and stops when tilt lever is fixed.
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</attention3>
<torque>
<torqueitem id = "T6B002">
<t-part>
Steering column mounting lower nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
a
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
14
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
1.4
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
10.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
<torqueitem id = "T6B003">
<t-part>
Steering column mounting upper nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
b
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
14
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
1.4
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
10.5
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
<torqueitem id = "T6B004">
<t-part>
Steering column reinforce nut
</t-part>
<t-part1>
C
</t-part1>
<t-value1>
5.5
</t-value1>
<t-value2>
0.56
</t-value2>
<t-value3>
4.0
</t-value3>
</torqueitem>
</torque>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect steering lock connector (6).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect P/S control module connector (7).
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Attach steering column harness clamps (8) in place.
</ptxt>
<figure>
<graphic graphicname = "IBP60B620003.swf" width = "88.000mm" height = "101.327mm" ver = "01" gw = "204" gh = "271"/>
</figure>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Connect P/S control module connector.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install instrument cluster panel. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install steering lower shaft. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6206015"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install steering joint cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6206001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install knee air bag (Inflator) module (if equipped). 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A8206007"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install lighting switch and wiper switch.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Lighting switch: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9206019"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Wiper switch: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9406012"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install contact coil assembly. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A6206003"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Install steering column hole cover. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A9306001"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Enable air bag system. 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENBP70A8206002"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</s1>
</servinfosub>
</servinfo>
</servinfotype>
</configtype>
</servcat>
</section></manual></suzuki>
